                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Limestone facings from statue base, likely from an equestrian statue given its size. Front side: rectangular slab, carved entabulature around all sides with some damage particularly on top and left side, in relatively good condition, two cracks, one horizontal crack and another vertical. Left side: only fragments are left of this, consisting of five rectangular fragments. There is a large vertical crack on the bottom right fragment around 2/3rds of the way towards the right hand side of the fragment.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.limestone" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html">Limestone</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.statuebase" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html">Statue Base</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">119</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">165</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">18</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.fragmentary"/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Front: text centred in the middle of the entabulature, and it takes up almost all of the available space. Left: from the remaining fragments it appears the text was centred within the hollow entablature and it can be presumed that it takes up most of the available space but cannot be certain.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Front side: text is complete and legible. Text is significantly larger at the top, shrinking incrementally further down the lines with the bottom line slightly larger again. The handwriting appears consistent throughout, broad, wide and well-formed with triangular interpuncts. Left: much of this text is missing. The handwriting appears consistent, and the letters and well-formed, broad and wide. Use of tall "I"s in line 15. Use of triangular interpuncts.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line19">Lines 1–19</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">27–120</height>
                                </dimensions>
